Dogballs is a slang term used in the game of golf. Golfers who post a score equal to an eight on any one hole are said to have posted 'Dogballs'. The origin of the term is in reference to what the number eight (8) looks like on its side. An eight on its side has the appearance of a male dog's genitalia. Generally regarded as a very poor score, because the maximum number (par) for any golf hole is five, Dogballs is to be avoided at all costs.